<section class="about-banner">
    <div class="container">
        <div class="row d-flex align-items-center justify-content-center">
            <div class="about-content col-lg-12">
                <h1 class="text-white">
                    Customer Journey
                </h1>
                <p class="text-white link-nav"><a href="index">Home </a>  <span class="lnr lnr-arrow-right"></span>  <a href="#"> Customer Journey</a></p>
            </div>
        </div>
    </div>
</section>

<section class="post-content-area single-post-area">
    <div class="container">
        <div class="row">
            <div class="col-lg-8 posts-list">
                <div class="single-post row">
                    <div class="col-lg-12">

                        <div class="feature-img">
                            <img class="img-fluid" src="img/Customer_Journey.jpg" alt="">
                        </div>
                    </div>

                    <div class="col-lg-12 col-md-12">
                        <h3 class="mt-20 mb-20">Create Insight driven Journey Maps</h3>
                        <p class="excert">
                            Brands understand the key to successful business is cross channel customer experience as it makes it easy for customers to complete any desired activity on whatever medium they are most comfortable with.
                        <p>
                            However, the actual implementation or cross channel customer experience is a different story. In fact, for many, communications are still siloed. and these brands are missing out on a 43x uplift in brand visibility and customer engagement from cross channel communication efforts.
                        </p>
                        <p>
                            The cross channel customer experience is just as important for b2b brands as b2c ones. The success of a cross channel strategy relies on strong customer journey map.
                        </p>
                        <p>
                            What is a customer journey mapping and why is it so important? Put simply, it is a powerful tool that teaches brands about their customers. It describes customers' processes, needs and perceptions throughout their interactions and relationship with a brand. It tells a story about potential frustrations and experiences of customers.
                        </p>
                        <p>
                            One may find the idea of starting a customer journey map intimidating, It is certainly an eye-opening process, and there is some time investment required. However, if one follow this process brands can be truly effective:
                            <ul class="col-lg-12" style="list-style-type: decimal; padding-left: 30px">
                                <li style="padding-left: 15px">
                                    Create an initial map that includes personas, behaviors, touchpoints,
                                </li>
                                <li style="padding-left: 15px">attitudes, emotions, and enablers.</li>
                                <li style="padding-left: 15px">Evaluate these attitudes, prioritize the focus and biggest pain point. Then determine the impact.</li>
                                <li style="padding-left: 15px">Explore and clarify needs and drivers and examine your capabilities (roles and processes).</li>
                                <li style="padding-left: 15px">Brainstorm the desired transformation and innovation.</li>
                                <li style="padding-left: 15px">Design a new experience. Before going full steam ahead, do a reality check before designing the experience.</li>
                            </ul>
                        </p>

                    </div>
                    <div class="col-lg-12">
                        <div class="quotes">
                            With that in mind, there are three key takeaways to ensure true success:
                            <ul class="col-lg-12" style="list-style-type: decimal; padding-left: 30px">
                                <li style="padding-left: 15px">
                                    Cross-channel strategies are only effective when the customer journey for different personas are mapped out (data analytics is key).
                                </li>
                                <li style="padding-left: 15px">
                                    Customer journey mapping should be optimized continuously so marketers are giving the best experience to prospects and prospective customers.
                                </li>
                                <li style="padding-left: 15px">
                                    Each touchpoint needs to have a KPI that matches to the overall objective and is measurable where possible.
                                </li>
                            </ul>
                        </div>
                        <div class="row mt-30 mb-30">
                            <div class="col-12">
                                <img class="img-fluid" src="img/CustomerJourney.jpg" alt="CustomerJourney">

                            </div>

                            <div class="col-lg-12 mt-30">
                                Ultimately, customer journey mapping puts the customer in the bull’s eye of a marketer’s thinking and demonstrates the need for the entire brand to adapt.
                                However, to truly impact the customer experience, learnings from customer journey mapping must be taken and implemented.
                                This will ensure cross-channel marketing efforts reach consumers effectively with the message in the right place at the right time.
                            </div>
                        </div>
                    </div>
                </div>

                <div class="comment-form">
                    <h4>Leave a Comment</h4>
                    <form>
                        <div class="form-group form-inline">
                            <div class="form-group col-lg-6 col-md-12 name">
                                <input type="text" class="form-control" id="name" placeholder="Enter Name" onfocus="this.placeholder = ''" onblur="this.placeholder = 'Enter Name'">
                            </div>
                            <div class="form-group col-lg-6 col-md-12 email">
                                <input type="email" class="form-control" id="email" placeholder="Enter email address" onfocus="this.placeholder = ''" onblur="this.placeholder = 'Enter email address'">
                            </div>
                        </div>
                        <div class="form-group">
                            <input type="text" class="form-control" id="subject" placeholder="Subject" onfocus="this.placeholder = ''" onblur="this.placeholder = 'Subject'">
                        </div>
                        <div class="form-group">
                            <textarea class="form-control mb-10" rows="5" name="message" placeholder="Messege" onfocus="this.placeholder = ''" onblur="this.placeholder = 'Messege'" required=""></textarea>
                        </div>
                        <a href="#" class="primary-btn text-uppercase">Post Comment</a>
                    </form>
                </div>
            </div>
            <div class="col-lg-4 sidebar-widgets">
                <div class="widget-wrap">
                    <partial name="_TopPosts" />

                </div>
            </div>
        </div>
    </div>
</section>
